<div id="review_855316049" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/855316049" />
    <a title="Page Turning Book Junkie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23166907-page-turning-book-junkie"><img alt="Page Turning Book Junkie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1441444551p2/23166907.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/855316049?book_show_action=true">Feb 15, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Page Turning Book Junkie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Page Turning Book Junkie" href="/user/show/23166907-page-turning-book-junkie">Page Turning Book Junkie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20711399-finding-solace">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/23166907-page-turning-book-junkie?shelf=arc">arc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer855316049" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15480633297271790153">*ARC provided in exchange for honest review* Find your next fix: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.pageturningbookjunkie.blogspot.com'>http://www.pageturningbookjunkie.blog...</a><br/><br/>4 out of 5 Emotional Gripping, It&apos;s Raining Hot Men, Passionate Stars!<br/><br/><span>[image error]</span><img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1393332043i/8696036._SX540_.jpg' alt=' photo image_zpsb46b9e6c.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>Wowza...wide range of emotions that a normal person would need some sort of decoder ring to decipher! This is another unexpected debut novel by a new author that will definitely leave it&apos;s mark on you. I think I just found my new favorite indulgence...stumbling upon new authors that blow my mind with well writt</span>
  <span id="freeText15480633297271790153" style="display:none">*ARC provided in exchange for honest review* Find your next fix: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.pageturningbookjunkie.blogspot.com">http://www.pageturningbookjunkie.blog...</a><br><br>4 out of 5 Emotional Gripping, It's Raining Hot Men, Passionate Stars!<br><br><span>[image error]</span><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1393332043i/8696036._SX540_.jpg" alt=" photo image_zpsb46b9e6c.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Wowza...wide range of emotions that a normal person would need some sort of decoder ring to decipher! This is another unexpected debut novel by a new author that will definitely leave it's mark on you. I think I just found my new favorite indulgence...stumbling upon new authors that blow my mind with well written amazing books I didn't see coming! Hey, it's gratifying and doesn't come with the added calories my chocolate fudge brownie packs. If you wouldn't have told me that this was Barbara Speak's first novel, I would have never been the wiser. The story was gripping and emotional...everything to keep you pleasantly frustrated and on the edge of your love seat. Colton and Sadie's connection was complicated, passionate, and deep. The emotional layers were stacked up and you just knew that eventually it will all come crashing down, but you couldn't tear your eyes or heart away even if you tried. After being involved in an abusive relationship, Sadie was still trying to find her place and decipher her inner insecurities and emotions. This is the story of her journey to healing and all the unsuspecting pitfalls that lie ahead.<br><br>"Having sex with different guys but never getting attached, meant that we could still be friends but they would always come back for more. And with each time, I felt a sense of power. However, lately I had been feeling different. I really didn't want the power, I just didn't want them to have it either. Finding that balance was tricker than I thought." -Sadie<br><br>While Sadie was still battered and bruised on the inside from her previous relationship, she tried to find her way back into the light. She had a great group of friends and a job that she loved. After one night of uninhibited drinking, she awoke to a foreign bed and a sexy man, which she apparently had a wildly hot night with. Unfortunately, all she could remember about him was her not so gracious introduction from the night before. Colt is devastatingly hot and eager to get more of Sadie. He becomes her guide into her emotional journey of self discovery. Colt finds a way to make Sadie feel strong, confident, and cherished. Colt has his own baggage and has come back to school for a second chance at his missed youth. Due to his current state of mind, their relationship is kept casual, but is nonetheless profound to them both no matter how much they attempted to disguise it from everyone, including themselves.<br><br>"Well then listen here woman. I've had to sit back and watch every dick head here tonight talk to you, touch you, dance with you. Eyeball you like they are going to fuck you. It is my turn. I need you Sadie. It's past want. Please come home with me. I'm not asking for sex. I just need you tonight. Please." -Colt<br><br>Colt and Sadie continue to play their emotional game of cat and mouse back and forth, with Colt pulling away every time things got too deep. Sadie struggles to burry her true feelings for Colt in order to keep him in her life. The effect that Colt has on her is to intense to let him go, so she takes whatever he will give to her. While this internal battle tests her limits, she finds a bit of comfort in another willing new tall hunk of man meat. Ash was a delightful surprise to the already confused Sadie. <br><br>"You, my beautiful, are single handedly the most spectacular person I have ever met. The idea that not only do I get the opportunity to know you, but get to experience what we have together with you. I am one very lucky man Sadie. I don't take for granted what I get to share with you, but you need to take care of you first." -Colt<br><br>Ash was amazing to Sadie. He was a gentle and caring gentlemen wrapped in a hot sexy package. Let the swooning commence. Ash is determined to do things right with Sadie, because he wants her true emotions. Can Sadie ever truly let go of Colt? Will Ash's patience be strong enough to wait for something that may never happen? Will Colt finally let go of his misguided views and admit his true feelings? Or will it all come to late? So many questions and possibilities. Fate for many people can be a hidden blessing, but for some it can be a cruel and unfair bitch. Timing is everything, and this story does a perfect job at showing you why.<br><br>"Everything I have been through so far has set me up for where I am now. I would not take back a thing. Mistakes can be the best learning experiences. The most important lesson I believe I have learned is, never be afraid to fail or you can never reach the goal you were trying to achieve. I could not be happier with how this chapter of my life turned out." -Sadie<br><br>This was a fantastic debut novel that I enjoyed every step of the way. Just when you think you have it all figured out and you are sure of the outcome...BAM! You get thrust into another direction you didn't see coming. My emotions were left a dizzy mess from being run through the spin cycle, but it just made me love the story all the more. With the amount of romance novels I have read, it is hard to still surprise me, and this book did a superb job. Keep your eye on this series and amazing author. She just released a novella for this series, Affliction (Finding Solace #1.5), which is Colt's side of the story. Hmmmm....I wonder what he has to say about all this mess?<br><br>Find me at: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.facebook.com/pageturningbookjunkie">http://www.facebook.com/pageturningbo...</a><br>Blog: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.pageturningbookjunkie.blogspot.com">http://www.pageturningbookjunkie.blog...</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="15480633297271790153" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


