<div id="review_736677152" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/736677152" />
    <a title="Kamila" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20069540-kamila"><img alt="Kamila" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/736677152?book_show_action=true">Oct 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kamila" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kamila" href="/user/show/20069540-kamila">Kamila</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer736677152" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12684950254350504138">THIS BOOK IS FANTASTIC!<br/> I really do not know where to start. The development of characters is superb. Sadie faces hard designs in her life and I was there living it with her. I cried, I laughed, I empathized all thanks to the down to earth story. There is so much love between those lines! I really admit to hating love triangles and but you can&apos;t help but understand and support Sadie&apos;s decision. Whats so great about this book is that it had me (I admit openly) bawlling for Sadie&apos;s love for Colt a</span>
  <span id="freeText12684950254350504138" style="display:none">THIS BOOK IS FANTASTIC!<br /> I really do not know where to start. The development of characters is superb. Sadie faces hard designs in her life and I was there living it with her. I cried, I laughed, I empathized all thanks to the down to earth story. There is so much love between those lines! I really admit to hating love triangles and but you can't help but understand and support Sadie's decision. Whats so great about this book is that it had me (I admit openly) bawlling for Sadie's love for Colt and radiantly smiling for her love for Ash. Its rare for a reader to not be biased towards a character, but Barbara makes it impossible through her writing to hate a character, because no matter what they are all so basically human. Great and difficult love story, passionate read, peaceful ending. Simply beautiful. I hope sincerely all of you pick up this book, because it is so worth it. Best of luck Barbara!!! &lt;3<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12684950254350504138" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


