        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer966836428" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1070685729724149129">Mistakes can be the best learning experiences...<br/>This was my first Barbara Speak read, but the first of many. I&apos;m a fan and looking forward to more in the Flawlessly Broken series. The author put me through the wringer with this story. I didn&apos;t just fall in love with the two main characters like in most books, I connected with a lot of characters. Barbara could write many books using her awesome cast of characters, but there&apos;s a very special one that ripped my heart out, I really NEED to read tha</span>
  <span id="freeText1070685729724149129" style="display:none">Mistakes can be the best learning experiences...<br />This was my first Barbara Speak read, but the first of many. I'm a fan and looking forward to more in the Flawlessly Broken series. The author put me through the wringer with this story. I didn't just fall in love with the two main characters like in most books, I connected with a lot of characters. Barbara could write many books using her awesome cast of characters, but there's a very special one that ripped my heart out, I really NEED to read that story, when it's time for him to shine. This was a very emotional journey, I was so torn because I could understand all sides but only one choice could be made, and Sadie made the right one. I especially enjoyed how Sadie talked directly to me while telling her story, her witty banter and internal dialogue was fun. And...Um...naked pizza night...best idea ever!</span>
