<div id="review_1124941653" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1124941653" />
    <a title="Tbird London" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20349967-tbird-london"><img alt="Tbird London" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396445601p2/20349967.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1124941653?book_show_action=true">Dec 06, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tbird London" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tbird London" href="/user/show/20349967-tbird-london">Tbird London</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1124941653" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2358056400766926843">Sadie a 20 year old hair dresser, who is nursing a crushed heart, had decided to fix her problems with sex and alcohol. I swear there are times I wonder if she isn’t an alcoholic the way she drinks, but she is also surrounded by a group of friends who seems to take care of her and make sure she is protected. One night she meets Colt, the sexy alpha male that I could never completely understand.<br/>One minute he is the man of our dreams, the next he just disappears for a week or more at a time. Sadie</span>
  <span id="freeText2358056400766926843" style="display:none">Sadie a 20 year old hair dresser, who is nursing a crushed heart, had decided to fix her problems with sex and alcohol. I swear there are times I wonder if she isn’t an alcoholic the way she drinks, but she is also surrounded by a group of friends who seems to take care of her and make sure she is protected. One night she meets Colt, the sexy alpha male that I could never completely understand.<br />One minute he is the man of our dreams, the next he just disappears for a week or more at a time. Sadie always took him back though. She played games with him as far as not letting him know he was getting to her, when she saw him with someone else she would try to make him jealous. During one of those times when she was going to assert her independence from Colt, she ran into Ash again. He was a few years older than her but they had met in high school.<br />He was drawn to Sadie immediately and treated her like a Princess. He was sending her flowers, taking her out, always being there. While she was experiencing this kind of love, Colt’s time had come to an end. It was time for goodbye for Sadie and Colt. You could tell they both loved each other but words continued to get in the way of expressing that. <br />By the end of the book Colt has come back, Ash is still very much in the picture and Sadie is left with a huge decision, who does she love versus who is she in love with. I know this sounds like a love triangle but it really isn’t. This is more of an unfortunate timing for Colt and a balance of trust for Ash. Sadie makes her choice and all I can say is I am glad I wasn’t in her shoes, because that was a difficult decision to make. <br />The story had many characters, so many at times it felt confusing keeping them all straight in the beginning but the author did a good job at developing each one into their role for the story. I would have happily given this a five star rating, except for one major problem I had. The book is so very long, yet the big scenes were solved so quickly. Within a few pages she had made the biggest choice of her life, yet we had to read so many pages of things that didn’t really add to the story. I give her major kudos for her writing style and the ability to put a story like this together, but next book, and yes I really hope there is a next book, I would love to see more event development instead of pages of details and description of issues that really don’t add to the story. <br />The author gave us everything we could ask for though in the emotion range. I laughed, wanted to cry a few times, left me on the edge of my seat for brief moments, intrigue and a wonderful love story. Sadie is a strong female character, one that we can all admire at times but I wished we had seen more of the actual story and less of the extras so we could have really invested our total attention to Sadie, Colt and Ash.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2358056400766926843" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
