<div id="review_822035013" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/822035013" />
    <a title="Angela " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14377998-angela"><img alt="Angela " src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/822035013?book_show_action=true">Jan 12, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Angela " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Angela " href="/user/show/14377998-angela">Angela </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer822035013" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer165547533394619349">I was given the pleasure of receiving an ARC (advance reading copy) of this book and it was truely a pleasure to read.<br/><br/>If you like roller coaster rides with twists and turns when you’re reading then this book is definatly for you because it contains twists and turns and when you think you’re on the right track bam another surprise turn. It will certainly keep you on your toes from start to finish. Its a book that will make you laugh, cry (so definatly have some tissues handy), groan, scream and k</span>
  <span id="freeText165547533394619349" style="display:none">I was given the pleasure of receiving an ARC (advance reading copy) of this book and it was truely a pleasure to read.<br /><br />If you like roller coaster rides with twists and turns when you’re reading then this book is definatly for you because it contains twists and turns and when you think you’re on the right track bam another surprise turn. It will certainly keep you on your toes from start to finish. Its a book that will make you laugh, cry (so definatly have some tissues handy), groan, scream and knock some sense into the characters.<br /><br />This stand alone novel follows the life of Sadie Warren, a victim of an abusive relationship who finds it hard to trust any man enough to have a relationship with. She finds it easier to have no-strings attached sex with various partners then get involved. Anyone that’s been in her shoes would probably make the same decision, so don’t judge!! That all changes when after getting drunk one night she ends up in bed with Colton, or Colt as he likes to be called. Their relationship is classed as “no-strings attached” until Sadie’s feeling develop into something more which turns out to be all one-sided. Colt is a complicated person who Sadie tries to give the benefit of doubt to, but in turn its all a waste.<br /><br />Just when you thought that Sadie is destined to end up alone and broken hearted all over again, enter Ash, the knight in shining Armour to rescue Sadie and walk off into the sunset to their happily ever after!!!<br /><br />This book is a definate must read! The main and supporting characters are superb and the emotion is real and heartfelt and almost make you feel like you’re a part of their journey from start to finish. I hate love triangles in books and even though I felt Sadie ended up with the wrong man, Im glad that she got her happily ever after.<br /><br />I’m looking forward to future books from Barbara Speak. If Finding Solace is anything to go by, then they’ll be awesome.<br /><br />**** out 5</span>
  <a data-text-id="165547533394619349" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


