<div id="review_847717217" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/847717217" />
    <a title="Jennifer Juers" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10559393-jennifer-juers"><img alt="Jennifer Juers" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1575998279p2/10559393.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/847717217?book_show_action=true">Feb 07, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer Juers" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer Juers" href="/user/show/10559393-jennifer-juers">Jennifer Juers</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/20711399-finding-solace">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer847717217" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer201674472314033952">I wish I could give more than a 5 star rating on this book, but that&apos;s the max!<br/><br/>I connected with Sadie&apos;s character right away. She talks to you, the reader while telling her story, which I have never come across in any book I&apos;ve read. Her choices, not so much. At times, I was laughing with her, yelling at her, and then crying with her. This book was an emotional roller coaster. There were happy times when things were going perfectly and then one decision would change it all. Someone would come in</span>
  <span id="freeText201674472314033952" style="display:none">I wish I could give more than a 5 star rating on this book, but that's the max!<br /><br />I connected with Sadie's character right away. She talks to you, the reader while telling her story, which I have never come across in any book I've read. Her choices, not so much. At times, I was laughing with her, yelling at her, and then crying with her. This book was an emotional roller coaster. There were happy times when things were going perfectly and then one decision would change it all. Someone would come into her life and make it better, but not necessarily complete. Who could complete that circle? Would she ever be fully happy? You've read about love triangles, yes? Well, you are going to find one and a little more in this book!<br /><br />Colt. This man was gorgeous bad-boy that refused to change for anyone. We had a love/hate relationship. The choices he made had me cringing in my seat. I wanted to smack him right upside his head. His ways made me want to throw my kindle and have a major talk with Sadie and ask her WTF was she thinking? In the end, would he make the ultimate sacrifice and commit?<br /><br />I loved Tony right away and thought that they would be together through it all. Unfortunately, my fairytale didn't come true. But can they have the best friendship that a male and female can have or will they be the worst of enemies?<br /><br />Then there was Ash. Mmmmm mmmmm mmmm. He has a way with words that would melt your heart. He also has the best way to make a pizza and you can't beat that! Trust me. Will he be the one to shine? Or will she break his heart?<br /><br />So which man will complete her circle? Will she have her happily ever after? Download the book today you won't regret it. <br /><br />Congrats Barbara for writing an excellent book that had me hooked from the first page! You must, must, must write more. </span>
  <a data-text-id="201674472314033952" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


