<div id="review_975797730" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/975797730" />
    <a title="Karen Benton" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19496479-karen-benton"><img alt="Karen Benton" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486492796p2/19496479.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/975797730?book_show_action=true">Jun 23, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Karen Benton" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Karen Benton" href="/user/show/19496479-karen-benton">Karen Benton</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer975797730" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17270269270840702775">Ever read a synopsis and think sounds good but familiar...yep I won&apos;t lie that&apos;s what I said to myself when I first saw this book. BOY was I wrong!!!<br/>This book was so different than the typical romance books we&apos;ve all been reading. What was so different you ask?? Well for starters...it wasn&apos;t predictable. I had to really pay attention or I would miss some important detail. It was emotional, heartfelt and absolutely possible in every day life.<br/>You ever read a book that you just can&apos;t get out of you</span>
  <span id="freeText17270269270840702775" style="display:none">Ever read a synopsis and think sounds good but familiar...yep I won't lie that's what I said to myself when I first saw this book. BOY was I wrong!!!<br />This book was so different than the typical romance books we've all been reading. What was so different you ask?? Well for starters...it wasn't predictable. I had to really pay attention or I would miss some important detail. It was emotional, heartfelt and absolutely possible in every day life.<br />You ever read a book that you just can't get out of your head? Hours, days pass and you are driving down the road and a song comes on and you instantly think of the characters and what they went through as if it were real?? Ahhh yeah totally happened to me today...only I didn't know who the song fit more Colt or Ash (sigh). I am dying to get my hands on the next book Fearing Regret so I don't have to feel this loss without them.<br />I connected with Sadie's story on a personal level...she had family and friends that adored her and gave with all her heart yet something was missing. That one thing that all women have dreamed about since they were little...their prince! Her desire leads her on a journey of highs and lows that will leave you scratching your head.It will have you asking yourself if you truly believe in fate, that all things good and bad happen for a reason?!?!What might have been... <br />I need more.....I want to hear Tony's story and what happens with Colt, Ash and Sadie. I feel like I am a part of their circle and have been left behind...lonely.<br /> <br />Amazing job Author Barbara Speak...everyone keep your eye on this one. I have a feeling it's just the beginning of a long, beautiful ride.<br /> <br />4 Heart wrenching "If it's meant to be it will be" stars!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17270269270840702775" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


