<div id="review_998618195" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/998618195" />
    <a title="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews"><img alt="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1464483219p2/12941902.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/998618195?book_show_action=true">Jul 16, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " class="user" itemprop="url" name="RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews " href="/user/show/12941902-relentlessbookchic-ramblings-reviews">RelentlessBookChic Ramblings &amp; Reviews </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer998618195" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15398114465047730579">Okay so my mind is telling me 4 but my heart is saying 5 so I am giving this 4.5 stars. <br/><br/>I love a book that makes me feel. A book that takes on a life and plays like a beautiful movie in my mind. This book did that for me. It was beautiful, tragic, fun and I felt like I was in the middle of it all. <br/><br/>Sadie is your normal everyday girl. She isn&apos;t perfect and she is just someone that I could relate to on every level. She was strong but made some stupid decisions all in the name of love. I understood </span>
  <span id="freeText15398114465047730579" style="display:none">Okay so my mind is telling me 4 but my heart is saying 5 so I am giving this 4.5 stars. <br /><br />I love a book that makes me feel. A book that takes on a life and plays like a beautiful movie in my mind. This book did that for me. It was beautiful, tragic, fun and I felt like I was in the middle of it all. <br /><br />Sadie is your normal everyday girl. She isn't perfect and she is just someone that I could relate to on every level. She was strong but made some stupid decisions all in the name of love. I understood those decision, I have made them too. She had a great group of friends with a strong bond and a great support system. <br /><br />Colt, the beautifully broken bad boy. I loved him, I hated him..there were times I wanted to throw my Kindle dealing with this man! But God did he break my heart sometimes and then mend it back together. He &amp; Sadie had one of those relationships, you know the ones! <br /><br />Ash, I love him. He.was.perfect. But like Sadie, I just had this special place for Colt. I am not one of those who always wants the bay boys to win the girl, no I was actually rooting for Ash..but I will let you read it to find out who got the girl ;) <br /><br />So did I take off the 1/2 star you ask...there were some parts in the dialogue where I had a hard time figuring out who was talking. Some parts were a little confusing but nothing major. I loved the story, I literally went to sleep with it in my hand every night because I was staying up way past my bedtime reading! <br /><br />Great job Barbara Speak..that is the way to come into the game. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15398114465047730579" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


