        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer733140236" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16316837233124528327">I received this book for free in exchange for an honest review. I was sucked into this story and the characters quickly, enjoying their everyday activities as much as the drama filled events throughout the book. This story delves into the life of Sadie and the relationships that make her who she is. Sadie comes across to others as a confident twenty year old however she has had some struggles in the past that she is eager to move on from. She is happy with her life, hanging out with great friend</span>
  <span id="freeText16316837233124528327" style="display:none">I received this book for free in exchange for an honest review. I was sucked into this story and the characters quickly, enjoying their everyday activities as much as the drama filled events throughout the book. This story delves into the life of Sadie and the relationships that make her who she is. Sadie comes across to others as a confident twenty year old however she has had some struggles in the past that she is eager to move on from. She is happy with her life, hanging out with great friends and not getting serious with anyone. This changes when she meets Colt who sweeps her off her feet ... or so she thinks.<br /><br />Sadie often frustrated me in her choices and behaviour as did Colt and I was happy when Ash arrived on the scene. Though of course this created an element of drama. The secondary characters were awesome in this story and very likable, from the men in Sadie's life especially the Harrison boys, Mike, Tony and Jason to Heather her roommate and closest friend. I really enjoyed the journey they all had together and the experiences they shared throughout the story. I recommend this book to all who love a characters journey of self discovery and the ups and downs in their life. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16316837233124528327" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


