<div id="review_940327715" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/940327715" />
    <a title="The Book Fairy Reviews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/16881583-the-book-fairy-reviews"><img alt="The Book Fairy Reviews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1406836721p2/16881583.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/940327715?book_show_action=true">May 17, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="The Book Fairy Reviews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="The Book Fairy Reviews" href="/user/show/16881583-the-book-fairy-reviews">The Book Fairy Reviews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer940327715" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13654730514053054024">Reading the journey of someones life is always interesting. You get to learn the mistakes they made, then ask yourself why would they do that?!? When they finally make the right choices, you know the healthy ones. You are right there with them yelling at the top of your lungs YES! So ladies if you are into reading books like that, then this is your book. Finding Solace is Sadie&apos;s journey to finding herself through bad choices, mistakes and then realizing what she has. I loved it. I cried with he</span>
  <span id="freeText13654730514053054024" style="display:none">Reading the journey of someones life is always interesting. You get to learn the mistakes they made, then ask yourself why would they do that?!? When they finally make the right choices, you know the healthy ones. You are right there with them yelling at the top of your lungs YES! So ladies if you are into reading books like that, then this is your book. Finding Solace is Sadie's journey to finding herself through bad choices, mistakes and then realizing what she has. I loved it. I cried with her , felt her frustration. I got mad at her for her decisions to continue when she shouldn't have. Yes ladies I felt like I was in the story trying to give Sadie advice. You know I have said it before, when you get lost in the fine line of reality and fiction is when you are reading a fabulous book. Barbara Speak has given us that fine line where you can and will lose your grip on reality. When you finish reading this I guarantee that you will be left mourning the loss of your fictional friends and family. You will read and love and treasure it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13654730514053054024" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


