        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer974321492" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8681690498380285905">4 stars *Reviewed for Crazy Daisy Book Whore*<br/><br/>One long roller coaster ride, but I didn&apos;t want it to end! <br/><br/>In Finding Solace, we meet 20-year old hair dresser Sadie Warren. She has survived a nightmare relationship but not without a guarded heart. Sadie meets Colt, a guy with a complicated life and a guarded heart too. He challenges Sadie to see herself in a different way, stronger and more open. Enter Ash, swoon, who sees Sadie as the strong beauty she has become. <br/><br/>Will Colt&apos;s &quot;friends with benefit</span>
  <span id="freeText8681690498380285905" style="display:none">4 stars *Reviewed for Crazy Daisy Book Whore*<br /><br />One long roller coaster ride, but I didn't want it to end! <br /><br />In Finding Solace, we meet 20-year old hair dresser Sadie Warren. She has survived a nightmare relationship but not without a guarded heart. Sadie meets Colt, a guy with a complicated life and a guarded heart too. He challenges Sadie to see herself in a different way, stronger and more open. Enter Ash, swoon, who sees Sadie as the strong beauty she has become. <br /><br />Will Colt's "friends with benefits" arrangement be enough to satisfy Sadie, or will she let Ash sweep her off her feet? <br /><br />I loved the characters and friendships developed throughout this book. There are so many of them that I'd love to read more about. This book, however, is not for the feint of heart. It had ups and downs, and I nearly threw my kindle across the room at one point. That just makes me love Barbara even more! I loved the unpredictability of this story. It was a very long, fully developed story. This is definitely worth the read!</span>
  <a data-text-id="8681690498380285905" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
